=H= Configuration

=h= Show information

Devices and dns status:         ‹nmcli›
NetworkManager status:          ‹nmcli g›
Networking status:              ‹nmcli n›
Show connections:               ‹nmcli con›
Show all devices status:        ‹nmcli dev›
Show all devices info:          ‹nmcli dev sh›

=h= Control

Enable/disable networking:                ‹nmcli n [on/off]›
Enable/disable type of connection:        ‹nmcli r [type] [on|off]›
    Types: wifi, wwan, all

=h= Connection properties

Most used connection properties and values:
‹ipv4.method manual                    ›IPv4 address configured statically
‹ipv4.method auto                      ›Configuration settings from a DHCPv4 server
‹ipv4.address "192.168.0.10/24"        ›Static IPv4 address, network prefix
‹ipv4.gateway 192.168.0.1              ›IPv4 Gateway
‹ipv4.dns 8.8.8.8                      ›Modify /etc/resolv.conf to use this nameserver
‹connection.autoconnect yes            ›Automatically activate this connection on boot
‹connection.id eth0                    ›Name of the connection
‹connection.interface-name             ›Bind connection to the network interface

=H= Examples

Add IP to DNS servers list:        ‹nmcli con mod eno1 +ipv4.dns 8.8.4.4›
Add new connection:                ‹nmcli con add type ethernet connection.interface-name enp1s0›
Disconnect the interface:          ‹nmcli dev disconnect enp0s8›
Unmanage the interface:            ‹nmcli device set enp0s8 managed no›

Configure static IP address:‹
nmcli con modify eno1 ipv4.addresses "192.168.0.100/24 192.168.0.1"
nmcli con modify eno1 ipv4.method manual
nmcli con down eno1 && nmcli con up eno1
nmcli device show eno1›

Configure DHCP:‹
nmcli con modify eno1 ipv4.method auto
nmcli con down eno1 && nmcli con up eno1
nmcli device show eno1›

Connect to wifi:‹
nmcli radio wifi on
sudo nmcli dev wifi rescan
nmcli dev wifi list
sudo nmcli --ask dev wifi connect NETWORK_NAME
nmcli dev status
nmcli con show›
